OL,3,CHealth service ombudsman visits town
OL,4,Cafter receiving 100 complaints
OL,6,FMrs Ashford died from a stroke in 2015
OL,7,Fafter being told her tumour was not
OL,8,Fgrowing, despite MRI scans showing it
OL,9,Fwas pushing her brain to one side.
OL,11,FA subsequent investigation found that
OL,12,Fshe was offered surgery too late.
OL,14,FHer husband Alan Ashford said: "It was
OL,15,Fhorrific. They just left the tumour to
OL,16,Fconsume her."
OL,18,FHe added: "I blame myself because I
OL,19,Fjust trusted him (the doctor)."
