OL,3,CHealth service ombudsman visits town
OL,4,Cafter receiving 100 complaints
OL,6,FThe Ombudsman's 2021 report on NHS
OL,7,Fimaging highlighted repeated failings
OL,8,Fsuch as those found in Mrs Ashford's
OL,9,Fcase.
OL,11,FRob Behrens said: "By visiting the
OL,12,Fcoastal town, we hope to learn from
OL,13,Fresidents and organisations to
OL,14,Funderstand why some people face
OL,15,Fbarriers in complaining.
OL,17,F"I believe in the power of
OL,18,Fcomplaining. A complaint has the power
OL,19,Fto reveal the truth, bring closure and
OL,20,Fcreate lasting positive change.
